data.chText: （名词或动词的）复数，复数形式
data.enText: a form of a noun or verb that refers to more than one person or thing

data.chText: 这个动词应该用复数形式。
data.enText: The verb should be in the plural .
connected with or having the plural form

data.chText: 英语中多数复数名词以s结尾。
data.enText: Most plural nouns in English end in ‘s’.
a plural society (= one with more than one racial , religious, etc. group)

means: (名词或动词的)复数，复数形式

tr: the form of a word that is used to denote more than one
grammatical number category referring to two or more items or units
composed of more than one member, set, or kind

value.def: The plural form of a word is the form that is used when referring to more than one person or thing.

example.ex: 'Data' is the Latin plural form of 'datum'.
example.tran: data 在拉丁文中是 datum 的复数形式。
他对复数代词 we 的使用

value.def: The plural of a noun is the form of it that is used to refer to more than one person or thing.

example.tran: person 的复数形式是什么？

value.def: A plural society or system involves different kinds of people.

example.ex: Britain is a plural society in which the secular predominates...
example.tran: 英国是个世俗主导的多元社会。

example.ex: His government has pledged to move the country towards a plural democracy.
example.tran: 他的政府已承诺要推动本国朝着多元民主的方向发展。
